      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented release notes and regression test suite.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was used under ISO 9001-certified QMS. Solver release notes, regression test results, and version-controlled case files are archived. Achieved level exceeds required level for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations through benchmark test cases.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against standard CFD benchmark problems including lid-driven cavity and backward-facing step. Published verification documentation from the vendor was reviewed and found satisfactory for the laminar and turbulent flow regimes relevant to CPB pump operation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "GCI for primary QoI (hemolysis index) must be below 5% between successive refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across three levels. GCI of 1.8% computed between medium and fine meshes using Richardson extrapolation. Discretization error is well controlled and the medium mesh (5.8M cells) was adopted for all production simulations."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match the simulated operating envelope within documented tolerances for flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid properties.",
      "rationale": "In-vitro experiments were conducted using a blood analog fluid (glycerol-water solution, viscosity matched to 37°C whole blood) in a closed-loop circuit. Flow rate and rotational speed were controlled within ±2% of target values. Boundary conditions in the CFD model were set to match measured experimental values directly."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index must agree with experimental measurements within ±15% across the primary operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Agreement within ±12% was achieved at 4 of 5 operating points. A deviation of 19% was observed at the low-flow, high-speed operating point. This point lies at the boundary of the validated operating envelope and is associated with a known limitation of the power-law hemolysis model under extreme shear conditions. The limitation is acknowledged and the overall assessment is considered acceptable, though the specific basis for accepting this residual discrepancy in the context of the CPB COU decision is not elaborated further."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The simulated QoI (relative hemolysis index RH) must directly correspond to the clinical and regulatory decision metric.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index (RH) is the primary regulatory metric for CPB device comparison against a predicate. The CFD model outputs volume-averaged hemolysis index computed from the power-law Giersiepen-Wurzinger model, which maps directly to the RH comparison criterion (RH < 1). QoI relevance is confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use geometry, fluid, and operating conditions representative of the CPB COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation was performed on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry under CPB-representative flow rates (2–6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000–3500 RPM). Blood analog fluid properties were matched. The validation domain sufficiently covers the COU operating space, supporting relevance of the validation evidence to the intended CPB decision context."
    },
    {
